.SH NAME
HTMLTableColElement.span \- HTMLTableColElement: span property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]span\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLTableColElement\f[R] interface represents the number of
columns this \f[CR]<col>\f[R] or \f[CR]<colgroup>\f[R] must span; this
lets the column occupy space across multiple columns of the table.
It reflects the \f[CR]span\f[R] attribute.
.SH VALUE
A positive number representing the number of columns.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] When setting a new value, the value is \f[I]clamped\f[R]
to the nearest strictly positive number (up to 1000).
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
This example provides two buttons to modify the column span of the first
cell of the body.
